Products
Consumer banking, corporate banking, credit cards, mortgage loans


Revenue
 US$ 295 million (past four quarters as September 2016)



Net income

 US$ 43 million (past four quarters as September 2016)


Total assets
 US$ 5.6 billion (2016)[1]


Total equity
 US$ 514.8 million (2015)[1]



Number of employees

1,304 (2015)[1]


Website
amerisbank.com


Ameris Bancorp is an American financial holding company headquartered in Jacksonville, Florida.[3][4] Ameris provides retail and commercial banking services to its customers in Georgia, Alabama, Florida, South Carolina and Tennessee through its wholly owned subsidiary Ameris Bank.[5] Ameris Bancorp was incorporated on December 18, 1980 as ABC Holding Company to act as parent company to American Banking Company. As of December 31, 2015, Ameris had approximately $5.59 billion in total assets, $4.02 billion in total loans, $4.88 billion in total deposits and $514.8 million in stockholder equity.[1]



Contents


1 Current Operations
2 History

2.1 Key dates


3 References
4 External links



Current Operations[edit]
Ameris Bancorp operations include a range of retail and commercial banking services, including checking and savings deposits, commercial and consumer loans, trust services, discount brokerage services, and electronic funds transfer services.[6]
History[edit]
Key dates[edit]

1971: American Banking Company founded.[7]
1980: ABC Holding Company forms as parent company to American Banking Company.[7]
1986: ABC Holding Company changes its name to ABC Bancorp.[7]
1987: ABC Bancorp initiates public stock offerings.[7]
1994: ABC Bancorp begins being publicly traded on the NASDAQ Exchange.[7]
1996: ABC Bancorp expansion into Alabama.[7]
2000: ABC Bancorp expansion into Florida.[7]
2005: ABC Bancorp rebrands as Ameris Bancorp.[7]
2006: Ameris expansion into South Carolina.[7]
2008: US Treasury purchases 52,000 shares of Ameris Preferred Stock as part of the Capital Purchase Program (CPP), in connection with the Troubled Asset Relief Program (TARP).[1]
2009: Ameris acquired all assets and liabilities of American United Bank from the FDIC.[1]
2009: Ameris acquired all assets and liabilities of United Security Bank from the FDIC.[1]
2010: Ameris acquired all assets and liabilities of Satilla Community Bank from the FDIC.[1]
2010: Ameris acquired all assets and liabilities of First Bank of Jacksonville from the FDIC.[1]
2010: Ameris acquired all assets and liabilities of Darby Bank & Trust from the FDIC.[1]
2010: Ameris acquired all assets and liabilities of Tifton Banking Company from the FDIC.[1]
2011: Ameris acquired all assets and liabilities of One Georgia Bank from the FDIC.[1]
2011: Ameris acquired all assets and liabilities of High Trust Bank from the FDIC.[1]
2012: Ameris acquired all assets and liabilities of Central Bank of Georgia from the FDIC.[1]
2012: US Treasury sells all 52,000 shares of Ameris Preferred Stock in an effort to wind down its remaining TARP bank investments.
2012: Ameris acquired all assets and liabilities of Montgomery Bank & Trust from the FDIC.[1]
2013: Ameris acquired Prosperity Banking Company for approximately $24.5 million.[1]
2014: Ameris acquired Coastal Bankshares for approximately $37.3 million.[1]
2014: Ameris reacquired all 52,000 shares of outstanding Preferred Shares after the US Treasury sold to private investors in 2012.[1]
2015: Ameris acquired Merchants & Southern Banks of Florida for $50.0 million.[1]
2015: Ameris acquired 18 bank branches from Bank of America in North Florida and South Georgia.[1]
2015: Ameris acquired Jacksonville Bancorp.[1]
2016: Ameris moves its executive team to new offices in Jacksonville, Florida.[3]
2016: Ameris Bancorp was ranked 76th in 'Fortune's 100 Fastest-Growing Companies' list.[8]

